---
layout: post
title: "Bishop Malkhaz Peace Project film showing in Bath"
date: 2026-02-26
---

Imagine a Christian Cathedral that responds to growing hatred and intolerance by constructing a synagogue and a mosque to bring faiths together. That's exactly what Bishop Malkhaz Songulashvili has done in Tbilisi, Georgia. 
![Poster for BathIFG showing 28 March at Building of Bath Museum of the film I will build this world with love](/assets/images/Malkhaz.jpg)Now Bath IFG, in collaboration with Bath Preservation Trust, is excited to present one of the only UK showings of a new film about the Peace Project. You can even meet Bishop Malkhaz, who will join us for the showing. It's 1600 on 28 March at the Museum of Bath Architecture, The Countess of Huntingdon's Chapel, The Vineyards.
Meanwhile in April a small group of Bath IFG members is taking a pilgrimage to Tbilisi to share Easter celebrations in the Peace Project and visit sacred sites in Georgia as guests of Bishop Malkhaz. It's still possible to join us for this trip 8-15 Apr: 
[details here](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1xX8yoiPsTYkn2oxoPZCuBeraLo_I7usGWG9uxcPGhyE/edit?tab=t.0#heading=h.tav1m0tnkjq8) Email us at the address below if interested. 

